Source: cdrom-detect
Section: debian-installer
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Debian Install System Team <debian-boot@lists.debian.org>
Uploaders: Petter Reinholdtsen <pere@debian.org>
Build-Depends-Indep: debhelper (>= 4.2.0), dpkg-dev (>= 1.7.0), po-debconf (>= 0.5.0)

Package: cdrom-detect
XC-Package-Type: udeb
Architecture: all
Depends: hw-detect
XB-Installer-Menu-Item: 14
Description: Detect CDROM devices and mount the CD
 This udeb will try to detect CDROM device. It will automatically insert
 the corresponding modules in the kernel and will mount the
 Debian Installation CD on /cdrom.
 .
 cdrom-detect is a minimal package used by debian-installer.
